adaptability.name: Adaptability
adaptability.effect: Adaptability increases the effectiveness of STAB moves from the usual 1.5× to 2×.
adaptability.desc: Powers up moves of the same type as the Pokémon.

aftermath.name: Aftermath
aftermath.effect: If an attacker faints a Pokémon with Aftermath using a contact move, the attacker will lose 1⁄4 of their maximum HP.
aftermath.desc: Damages the attacker if it knocks out the Pokémon with a move that makes direct contact.

air-lock.name: Air Lock
air-lock.effect: Air Lock suppresses all effects brought on by weather, including move power increases, end-of-turn damage, accuracy changes, relevant abilities and so on.

analytic.name: Analytic
analytic.effect: Boosts move power when the Pokémon moves last.
analytic.desc: Boosts the power of the Pokémon's move if it is the last to act that turn.

anger-point.name: Anger Point
anger-point.effect: Anger Point raises the ability-bearer's Attack to its maximum level - +6 stages or 4× usual power - when a move targeting it receives a critical hit.
anger-point.desc: The Pokémon is angered when it takes a critical hit, and that maxes its Attack stat.

anger-shell.name: Anger Shell
anger-shell.effect: When the Pokémon's HP drops below half, Anger Shell lowers its Defense and Special Defense but its Attack, Special Attack and Speed are raised.
anger-shell.desc: When an attack causes its HP to drop to half or less, the Pokémon gets angry. This lowers its Defense and Sp. Def stats but boosts its Attack, Sp. Atk, and Speed stats.

anticipation.name: Anticipation
anticipation.effect: A Pokémon with Anticipation will shudder upon entering battle, if an opponent has a move that is super-effective against it, or a One-Hit-KO move (Fissure, Horn Drill, Guillotine or Sheer Cold). It only activates when the ability-bearer switches in, not when an opponent switches in.
anticipation.desc: The Pokémon can sense an opposing Pokémon's dangerous moves.

arena-trap.name: Arena Trap
arena-trap.effect: Arena Trap prevents opponents from fleeing or switching out. Raised Pokémon are not affected. Raised Pokémon are any Flying types or those under the effects of Levitate, Magnet Rise or Telekinesis. Full details in glossary.
arena-trap.desc: Prevents opposing Pokémon from fleeing from battle.

armor-tail.name: Armor Tail
armor-tail.effect: Armor Tail prevents the opponent from using any moves that have priority, such as Quick Attack.
armor-tail.desc: The mysterious tail covering the Pokémon's head makes opponents unable to use priority moves against the Pokémon or its allies.

aroma-veil.name: Aroma Veil
aroma-veil.effect: Protects allies from attacks that limit their move choices.
aroma-veil.desc: Protects the Pokémon and its allies from effects that prevent the use of moves.

as-one.name: As One
as-one.effect: Combines Unnerve and Chilling Neigh/Grim Neigh
as-one.desc: This Ability combines the effects of both Calyrex's Unnerve Ability and Glastrier's/Spectrier's Chilling Neigh/Grim Neigh Ability.

bad-dreams.name: Bad Dreams
bad-dreams.effect: Bad Dreams causes all sleeping opponents to lose 1⁄8 of their maximum HP at the end of each turn.
bad-dreams.desc: Damages opposing Pokémon that are asleep.

battery.name: Battery
battery.effect: Battery allows the Pokémon to raise the power of teammates' special moves.
battery.desc: Powers up ally Pokémon's special moves.

battle-armor.name: Battle Armor
battle-armor.effect: Battle Armor prevents the Pokémon from receiving a critical hit.
battle-armor.desc: Hard armor protects the Pokémon from critical hits.

beads-of-ruin.name: Beads of Ruin
beads-of-ruin.effect: Lowers Special Defense of all Pokémon except itself.
beads-of-ruin.desc: The power of the Pokémon's ruinous beads lowers the Sp. Def stats of all Pokémon except itself.

berserk.name: Berserk
berserk.effect: Berserk raises the Pokémon's Special Attack by one stage when its HP falls below 50%.
berserk.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's Sp. Atk stat when it takes a hit that causes its HP to drop to half or less.

big-pecks.name: Big Pecks
big-pecks.effect: Big Pecks prevents the ability-bearer's Defense stat from being lowered, for example via Tail Whip.
big-pecks.desc: Prevents the Pokémon from having its Defense stat lowered.

blaze.name: Blaze
blaze.effect: Blaze increases the power of Fire-type moves by 50% (1.5×) when the ability-bearer's HP falls below a third of its maximum (known in-game as in a pinch).
blaze.desc: Powers up Fire-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low.

bulletproof.name: Bulletproof
bulletproof.effect: Bulletproof makes the Pokémon immune to ball and bomb moves.
bulletproof.desc: Protects the Pokémon from ball and bomb moves.

cheek-pouch.name: Cheek Pouch
cheek-pouch.effect: Cheek Pouch restores the bearer's HP when a Berry is consumed, on top of the berry's usual effects.
cheek-pouch.desc: The Pokémon's HP is restored when it eats any Berry, in addition to the Berry's usual effect.

chilling-neigh.name: Chilling Neigh
chilling-neigh.effect: Boosts Attack after knocking out a Pokémon.
chilling-neigh.desc: When the Pokémon knocks out a target, it utters a chilling neigh, which boosts its Attack stat.

chlorophyll.name: Chlorophyll
chlorophyll.effect: Chlorophyll doubles the ability-bearer's Speed during bright sunshine.
chlorophyll.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in harsh sunlight.

clear-body.name: Clear Body
clear-body.effect: Prevents other Pokémon from lowering its stats.
clear-body.desc: Prevents other Pokémon's moves or Abilities from lowering the Pokémon's stats.

cloud-nine.name: Cloud Nine
cloud-nine.effect: Cloud Nine suppresses all effects brought on by weather, including move power increases, end-of-turn damage, accuracy changes, relevant abilities and so on.

comatose.name: Comatose
comatose.effect: Comatose causes the Pokémon to behave as if it were asleep, though it doesn't officially have the Sleep status condition. It can still use its regular moves, but cannot be inflicted with any major status condition (sleep, poison, paralysis, burn, or freeze).
comatose.desc: The Pokémon is always drowsing and will never wake up. It can attack while in its sleeping state.

commander.name: Commander
commander.effect: Goes inside the mouth of an ally Dondozo if one is on the field.
commander.desc: When the Pokémon enters a battle, it goes inside the mouth of an ally Dondozo if one is on the field. The Pokémon then issues commands from there.

competitive.name: Competitive
competitive.effect: Competitive raises the ability-bearer's Special Attack by two stages when hit by a stat-lowering move.
competitive.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's Sp. Atk stat sharply when its stats are lowered by an opposing Pokémon.

compound-eyes.name: Compound Eyes
compound-eyes.effect: Compound Eyes raises the ability-bearer's accuracy by 30%.
compound-eyes.desc: The Pokémon's compound eyes boost its accuracy.

contrary.name: Contrary
contrary.effect: Makes stat changes have an opposite effect.
contrary.desc: Reverses any stat changes affecting the Pokémon so that attempts to boost its stats instead lower them— and attempts to lower its stats will boost them.

corrosion.name: Corrosion
corrosion.effect: Corrosion allows the bearer to poison any Pokémon, including Steel and Poison types.
corrosion.desc: The Pokémon can poison the target even if it's a Steel or Poison type.

costar.name: Costar
costar.effect: Copies ally's stat changes on entering battle.
costar.desc: When the Pokémon enters a battle, it copies an ally's stat changes.

cud-chew.name: Cud Chew
cud-chew.effect: Cud Chew causes the Pokémon to reuse an already consumed Berry at the end of the next turn.
cud-chew.desc: When the Pokémon eats a Berry, it will regurgitate that Berry at the end of the next turn and eat it one more time.

curious-medicine.name: Curious Medicine
curious-medicine.effect: Resets all stat changes upon entering battlefield.
curious-medicine.desc: When the Pokémon enters a battle, it scatters medicine from its shell, which removes all stat changes from allies.

cursed-body.name: Cursed Body
cursed-body.effect: May disable a move used on the Pokémon.
cursed-body.desc: May disable a move that has dealt damage to the Pokémon.

cute-charm.name: Cute Charm
cute-charm.effect: If a Pokémon with Cute Charm is hit by a move that makes contact, there is a 30% chance the attacker will become infatuated. It will not infatuate Pokémon of the same gender, genderless Pokémon, nor those with the ability Oblivious.
cute-charm.desc: The Pokémon may infatuate attackers that make direct contact with it.

damp.name: Damp
damp.effect: Damp prevents all Pokémon on the field from using the moves Selfdestruct and Explosion. It also prevents damage (to the Damp Pokémon only) from the ability Aftermath.
damp.desc: The Pokémon dampens its surroundings, preventing all Pokémon from using explosive moves such as Self-Destruct.

dancer.name: Dancer
dancer.effect: When another Pokémon on the field uses any Dance move, Dancer causes the ability-bearer to use that same move immediately afterward. They will still use their own move originally selected, at the usual time (e.g. after the opponent if they are slower).
dancer.desc: Whenever a dance move is used in battle, the Pokémon will copy the user to immediately perform that dance move itself.

dauntless-shield.name: Dauntless Shield
dauntless-shield.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's Defense stat the first time the Pokémon enters a battle.

dazzling.name: Dazzling
dazzling.effect: Dazzling makes the Pokémon immune to high-priority moves (i.e. those with a priority above 0).
dazzling.desc: The Pokémon dazzles its opponents, making them unable to use priority moves against the Pokémon or its allies.

defiant.name: Defiant
defiant.effect: Defiant raises the ability-bearer's Attack by two stages when hit by a stat-lowering move.
defiant.desc: If the Pokémon has any stat lowered by an opposing Pokémon, its Attack stat will be boosted sharply.

desolate-land.name: Desolate Land
desolate-land.effect: Desolate Land creates extremely harsh sunlight when the ability is activated (by Groudon reverting to its Primal form).
desolate-land.desc: The Pokémon changes the weather to nullify Water-type attacks.

disguise.name: Disguise
disguise.effect: Disguise allows the bearer to avoid damage for one attack, in a similar way to Substitute.
disguise.desc: Once per battle, the shroud that covers the Pokémon can protect it from an attack.

download.name: Download
download.effect: Download raises either the bearer's Attack or Special Attack by one stage when switching into battle, base on the opponent's defenses.
download.desc: The Pokémon compares an opposing Pokémon's Defense and Sp. Def stats before raising its own Attack or Sp. Atk stat—whichever will be more effective.

dragons-maw.name: Dragon's Maw
dragons-maw.effect: Dragon's Maw increases the power of Dragon-type moves used by this Pokémon by 50%.

drizzle.name: Drizzle
drizzle.effect: Drizzle creates a rain shower when the ability-bearer enters battle. The effect lasts 5 turns, unless it is cleared via Air Lock or Cloud Nine or replaced by another weather condition.
drizzle.desc: The Pokémon makes it rain when it enters a battle.

drought.name: Drought
drought.effect: Drought creates harsh sunlight when the ability-bearer enters battle. The effect lasts 5 turns, unless it is cleared via Air Lock or Cloud Nine or replaced by another weather condition.
drought.desc: Turns the sunlight harsh when the Pokémon enters a battle.

dry-skin.name: Dry Skin
dry-skin.effect:
Dry Skin causes several effects:
When hit by a Water-type attack, instead of damage it heals 1⁄4 of this Pokémon's maximum HP.
When hit by a Fire-type attack, it does 25% more damage.
During bright sunshine the Pokémon loses 1⁄8 of its maximum HP each turn.
During rain the Pokémon recovers 1⁄8 of its maximum HP each turn.
dry-skin.desc: Restores the Pokémon's HP in rain or when it is hit by Water-type moves. Reduces HP in harsh sunlight, and increases the damage received from Fire-type moves.

early-bird.name: Early Bird
early-bird.effect: The Pokémon awakens quickly from sleep.
early-bird.desc: The Pokémon awakens from sleep twice as fast as other Pokémon.

earth-eater.name: Earth Eater
earth-eater.effect: Restores HP when hit by a Ground-type move.
earth-eater.desc: If hit by a Ground-type move, the Pokémon has its HP restored instead of taking damage.

effect-spore.name: Effect Spore
effect-spore.effect: Contact may poison or cause paralysis or sleep.
effect-spore.desc: Contact with the Pokémon may inflict poison, sleep, or paralysis on the attacker.

electric-surge.name: Electric Surge
electric-surge.effect: Electric Surge creates a low-lying electric field, like the move Electric Terrain, when the Pokémon enters battle. It prevents grounded Pokémon from falling asleep, and increases the power of Electric type attacks.
electric-surge.desc: Turns the ground into Electric Terrain when the Pokémon enters a battle.

electromorphosis.name: Electromorphosis
electromorphosis.effect: If a Pokémon with Electromorphosis is hit by an attack, the power of the next Electric-type move it uses is doubled.
electromorphosis.desc: The Pokémon becomes charged when it takes damage, boosting the power of the next Electric-type move the Pokémon uses.

filter.name: Filter
filter.effect: Filter reduces the damage taken from super-effective attacks by 25%.
filter.desc: Reduces the power of supereffective attacks that hit the Pokémon.

flame-body.name: Flame Body
flame-body.effect: If a Pokémon with Flame Body is hit by a move that makes contact, there is a 30% chance the attacker will become burned.
flame-body.desc: Contact with the Pokémon may burn the attacker.

flare-boost.name: Flare Boost
flare-boost.effect: Powers up special attacks when burned.
flare-boost.desc: Powers up special moves when the Pokémon is burned.

flash-fire.name: Flash Fire
flash-fire.effect: When a Pokémon with Flash Fire is hit by a Fire-type move, it does not deal damage but instead raises the power of the bearer's Fire-type moves by 50%. Subsequent hits do not raise the power even more, but the effect remains while the ability-bearer is in battle.
flash-fire.desc: If hit by a Fire-type move, the Pokémon absorbs the flames and uses them to power up its own Fire-type moves.

flower-veil.name: Flower Veil
flower-veil.effect: Flower Veil prevents ally Grass-type Pokémon's stats from being lowered, in double and triple battles.
flower-veil.desc: Ally Grass-type Pokémon are protected from status conditions and the lowering of their stats.

fluffy.name: Fluffy
fluffy.effect: Fluffy reduces damage from contact moves by 50%, but Fire-type moves do double damage. Fire-type moves that make contact do regular damage.
fluffy.desc: Halves the damage taken from moves that make direct contact, but doubles that of Fire-type moves.

forewarn.name: Forewarn
forewarn.effect: Determines what moves a foe has.
forewarn.desc: When it enters a battle, the Pokémon can tell one of the moves an opposing Pokémon has.

frisk.name: Frisk
frisk.effect: The Pokémon can check a foe's held item.
frisk.desc: When it enters a battle, the Pokémon can check an opposing Pokémon's held item.

full-metal-body.name: Full Metal Body
full-metal-body.effect: Prevents other Pokémon from lowering its stats.
full-metal-body.desc: Prevents other Pokémon's moves or Abilities from lowering the Pokémon's stats.

fur-coat.name: Fur Coat
fur-coat.effect: Fur Coat reduces damage taken from physical attacks by 50%.
fur-coat.desc: Halves the damage from physical moves.

gale-wings.name: Gale Wings
gale-wings.desc: Gives priority to the Pokémon's Flying-type moves while its HP is full.

galvanize.name: Galvanize
galvanize.effect: Normal-type moves become Electric-type moves and their power boosted.
galvanize.desc: Normal-type moves become Electric-type moves. The power of those moves is boosted a little.

gluttony.name: Gluttony
gluttony.effect: A Pokémon with Gluttony will use a pinch berry when its HP drops to 50%, rather than the usual 25%.
gluttony.desc: If the Pokémon is holding a Berry to be eaten when its HP is low, it will instead eat the Berry when its HP drops to half or less.

good-as-gold.name: Good as Gold
good-as-gold.desc: A body of pure, solid gold gives the Pokémon full immunity to other Pokémon's status moves.

gooey.name: Gooey
gooey.effect: Contact with the Pokémon lowers the attacker's Speed stat.
gooey.desc: Contact with the Pokémon lowers the attacker's Speed stat.

grass-pelt.name: Grass Pelt
grass-pelt.effect: Boosts the Defense stat in Grassy Terrain.
grass-pelt.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's Defense stat on Grassy Terrain.

grassy-surge.name: Grassy Surge
grassy-surge.effect: Grassy Surge creates a low-lying grassy field, like the move Grassy Terrain, when the Pokémon enters battle. It restores the HP of grounded Pokémon each turn and increases the power of Grass type attacks.
grassy-surge.desc: Turns the ground into Grassy Terrain when the Pokémon enters a battle.

grim-neigh.name: Grim Neigh
grim-neigh.effect: Boosts Special Attack after knocking out a Pokémon.
grim-neigh.desc: When the Pokémon knocks out a target, it utters a terrifying neigh, which boosts its Sp. Atk stat.

guard-dog.name: Guard Dog
guard-dog.effect: Boosts Attack if intimidated, and prevents being forced to switch out.
guard-dog.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat if intimidated. Moves and items that would force the Pokémon to switch out also fail to work.

gulp-missile.name: Gulp Missile
gulp-missile.effect: Gulp Missile is the signature ability of Cramorant. If Cramorant uses the move Surf or Dive, it returns with a fish in its mouth. If Cramorant then takes damage, it retaliates by spitting out the fish, dealing extra damage.
gulp-missile.desc: When the Pokémon uses Surf or Dive, it will come back with prey. When it takes damage, it will spit out the prey to attack.

guts.name: Guts
guts.effect: Guts raises the ability-bearer's Attack by 50% when inflicted by a major status ailment (poison, burn, paralysis, freeze or sleep). If burnt, the Pokémon does not suffer the usual drop in Attack.
guts.desc: It's so gutsy that having a status condition boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat.

hadron-engine.name: Hadron Engine
hadron-engine.effect: Creates an Electric Terrain when entering battle, and boosts Special Attack while active.
hadron-engine.desc: Turns the ground into Electric Terrain when the Pokémon enters a battle. The futuristic engine within the Pokémon also boosts its Sp. Atk stat on Electric Terrain.

harvest.name: Harvest
harvest.effect: May create another Berry after one is used.
harvest.desc: May create another Berry after one is used.

healer.name: Healer
healer.effect: May heal an ally's status conditions.
healer.desc: Sometimes cures the status conditions of the Pokémon's allies.

heatproof.name: Heatproof
heatproof.effect: Heatproof reduces the damage taken from Fire-type moves by 50%. It also halves the damage from a burn, from 1⁄8 to 1⁄16 of the Pokémon's maximum HP.
heatproof.desc: The Pokémon's heatproof body halves the damage taken from Fire-type moves.

heavy-metal.name: Heavy Metal
heavy-metal.effect: Heavy Metal doubles the Pokémon's weight in battle. Increasing weight affects these moves:

honey-gather.name: Honey Gather
honey-gather.effect: Honey Gather has no effect in battle.
honey-gather.desc: The Pokémon may gather Honey after a battle.

hospitality.name: Hospitality
hospitality.effect: When the Pokémon enters a battle, it showers its ally with hospitality, restoring a small amount of the ally's HP.
hospitality.desc: When the Pokémon enters a battle, it showers its ally with hospitality, restoring a small amount of the ally's HP.

hunger-switch.name: Hunger Switch
hunger-switch.effect: Hunger Switch causes Morpeko to change its form each turn, alternating between Full Belly Mode and Hangry Mode. Morpeko's form also changes the type of its signature move, Aura Wheel.
hunger-switch.desc: The Pokémon changes its form, alternating between its Full Belly Mode and Hangry Mode after the end of every turn.

hustle.name: Hustle
hustle.effect: Hustle increases the ability-bearer's Attack by 50%, however, it also reduces the Accuracy of all Physical moves by 20%.
hustle.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat but lowers its accuracy.

hydration.name: Hydration
hydration.effect: A Pokémon with Hydration will cure itself of any status conditions during rain, at the end of each turn. This includes self-inflicted conditions such as from using Rest.
hydration.desc: Cures the Pokémon's status conditions in rain.

hyper-cutter.name: Hyper Cutter
hyper-cutter.effect: Hyper Cutter prevents the bearer's Attack stat from being lowered by other Pokémon, through moves such as Growl or abilities such as Intimidate.
hyper-cutter.desc: The Pokémon's prized, mighty pincers prevent other Pokémon from lowering its Attack stat.

ice-body.name: Ice Body
ice-body.effect: A Pokémon with Ice Body will recover 1⁄16 of its maximum HP during hail, after each turn. It also grants immunity to the hailstorm damage, if not already immune.
ice-body.desc: The Pokémon gradually regains HP in snow.

ice-face.name: Ice Face
ice-face.effect: Ice Face is the signature ability of Eiscue. It allows the Pokémon to take a physical attack without taking damage. After the attack, Eiscue changes to its No Ice Face form, however, it can be restored in hail.
ice-face.desc: The Pokémon's ice head can take a physical attack as a substitute, but the attack also changes the Pokémon's appearance. The ice will be restored when it snows.

ice-scales.name: Ice Scales
ice-scales.desc: The Pokémon is protected by ice scales, which halve the damage taken from special moves.

illuminate.name: Illuminate
illuminate.effect: Illuminate has no effect in battle.
illuminate.desc: Raises the likelihood of meeting wild Pokémon by illuminating the surroundings.

illusion.name: Illusion
illusion.effect: When a Pokémon with the Illusion ability switches into battle, it takes the form of the Pokémon in last place (6th) of the player's party. Illusion will not activate if the Pokémon in last place is the same species or is fainted.
illusion.desc: The Pokémon fools opponents by entering battle disguised as the last Pokémon in its Trainer's party.

immunity.name: Immunity
immunity.effect: Prevents the Pokémon from getting poisoned.
immunity.desc: The Pokémon's immune system prevents it from being poisoned.

imposter.name: Imposter
imposter.effect: It transforms itself into the Pokémon it is facing.
imposter.desc: The Pokémon transforms itself into the Pokémon it's facing.

infiltrator.name: Infiltrator
infiltrator.effect: Infiltrator ignores the effects of Reflect, Light Screen and Safeguard. In other words, if the opponent has used Safeguard, Toxic would still badly poison them.
infiltrator.desc: The Pokémon's moves are unaffected by the target's barriers, substitutes, and the like.

inner-focus.name: Inner Focus
inner-focus.effect: Inner Focus prevents the Pokémon from flinching, for example when attacked by a move like Headbutt.
inner-focus.desc: The Pokémon's intense focus prevents it from flinching or being affected by Intimidate.

insomnia.name: Insomnia
insomnia.effect: Insomnia prevents the ability-bearer from falling asleep, both from moves by other Pokémon like Sing, and self-inflicted sleep like Rest.
insomnia.desc: The Pokémon's insomnia prevents it from falling asleep.

intimidate.name: Intimidate
intimidate.effect: Intimidate lower's the Attack of all opponents by one stage when the ability-bearer switches in (including the start of a battle).
intimidate.desc: When the Pokémon enters a battle, it intimidates opposing Pokémon and makes them cower, lowering their Attack stats.

intrepid-sword.name: Intrepid Sword
intrepid-sword.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat the first time the Pokémon enters a battle.

iron-fist.name: Iron Fist
iron-fist.effect: Iron Fist increases the power of all punching moves by 20%.

justified.name: Justified
justified.effect: Justified raises the ability-bearer's Attack by one stage when hit by a damaging Dark-type move.
justified.desc: When the Pokémon is hit by a Dark-type attack, its Attack stat is boosted by its sense of justice.

keen-eye.name: Keen Eye
keen-eye.effect: Keen Eye prevents the Pokémon from losing accuracy, for example from moves like Sand-Attack.
keen-eye.desc: The Pokémon's keen eyes prevent its accuracy from being lowered.

klutz.name: Klutz
klutz.effect: The Pokémon can't use any held items.
klutz.desc: The Pokémon can't use any held items.

leaf-guard.name: Leaf Guard
leaf-guard.effect: Leaf Guard prevents the bearer from succumbing to major status ailments (sleep, burns, poisoning, paralysis or freezing) during sunny weather.
leaf-guard.desc: Prevents status conditions in harsh sunlight.

levitate.name: Levitate
levitate.effect: Levitate causes the Pokémon to be raised (like Flying-type Pokémon).
levitate.desc: By floating in the air, the Pokémon receives full immunity to all Ground-type moves.

libero.name: Libero
libero.effect: Libero changes the Pokémon's type to that of its previously used attack.
libero.desc: Changes the Pokémon's type to the type of the move it's about to use. This works only once each time the Pokémon enters battle.

light-metal.name: Light Metal
light-metal.effect: Light Metal halves the Pokémon's weight in battle. Decreasing weight affects these moves:

lightning-rod.name: Lightning Rod
lightning-rod.effect: Lightning Rod forces all single-target Electric-type moves - used by any other Pokémon on the field - to target this Pokémon, and with 100% accuracy. This includes the status move Thunder Wave. The ability is most useful in double/triple battles.
lightning-rod.desc: The Pokémon draws in all Electric-type moves. Instead of taking damage from them, its Sp. Atk stat is boosted.

limber.name: Limber
limber.effect: The Pokémon is protected from paralysis.
limber.desc: The Pokémon's limber body prevents it from being paralyzed.

lingering-aroma.name: Lingering Aroma
lingering-aroma.effect: Contact changes the attacker's Ability to Lingering Aroma.
lingering-aroma.desc: Contact with the Pokémon changes the attacker's Ability to Lingering Aroma.

liquid-ooze.name: Liquid Ooze
liquid-ooze.effect: Damages attackers using any draining move.
liquid-ooze.desc: The strong stench of the Pokémon's oozed liquid damages attackers that use HP-draining moves.

liquid-voice.name: Liquid Voice
liquid-voice.effect: Liquid Voice causes all sound-based moves used by the Pokémon to become Water type. Water type Pokémon also gain STAB from those moves.

long-reach.name: Long Reach
long-reach.effect: The Pokémon uses its moves without making contact with the target.
long-reach.desc: The Pokémon uses its moves without making contact with the target.

magic-bounce.name: Magic Bounce
magic-bounce.desc: The Pokémon reflects status moves instead of getting hit by them.

magic-guard.name: Magic Guard
magic-guard.effect:
Magic Guard protects the Pokémon from indirect damage, including:
Damage from the Poison status condition
Damage from a Burn (though the Attack drop still occurs)
Damage from Leech Seed or Curse
Weather damage (hail or sandstorm)
Recoil damage (e.g. from Head Charge)
Crash damage from Jump Kick or High Jump Kick
Damage from Spikes or Stealth Rocks when switching in (Toxic Spikes still poisons the Pokémon but they will not lose HP)
HP loss from Life Orb (though the move boosts still occur)
It does not prevent damage from confusion, trapping moves (e.g. Bind) or Struggle.ChangesIn Generation 4 a Pokémon with Magic Guard cannot be poisoned from Toxic Spikes, nor become fully immobile through paralysis (though the Speed drop still occurs).
magic-guard.desc: The Pokémon only takes damage from attacks.

magician.name: Magician
magician.effect: The Pokémon steals the held item of a Pokémon it hits with a move.
magician.desc: The Pokémon steals the held item from any target it hits with a move.

magma-armor.name: Magma Armor
magma-armor.effect: Magma Armor prevents the Pokémon from becoming frozen, for example from moves like Blizzard.
magma-armor.desc: The Pokémon's hot magma coating prevents it from being frozen.

magnet-pull.name: Magnet Pull
magnet-pull.effect: Magnet Pull prevents Steel type Pokémon from switching out of battle or fleeing.
magnet-pull.desc: Prevents Steel-type Pokémon from fleeing by pulling them in with magnetism.

marvel-scale.name: Marvel Scale
marvel-scale.effect: Marvel Scale raises the ability-bearer's Defense by 50% when inflicted by a major status ailment (poison, burn, paralysis, freeze or sleep).
marvel-scale.desc: The Pokémon's marvelous scales boost its Defense stat if it has a status condition.

mega-launcher.name: Mega Launcher
mega-launcher.effect: Mega Launcher increases the power of all aura and pulse moves by 50%. Heal Pulse boosts the HP restored by 50%.

merciless.name: Merciless
merciless.effect: The Pokémon's attacks become critical hits if the target is poisoned.
merciless.desc: The Pokémon's attacks become critical hits if the target is poisoned.

minds-eye.name: Mind's Eye
minds-eye.effect: The Pokémon ignores changes to opponents' evasiveness, its accuracy can't be lowered, and it can hit Ghost types with Normal- and Fighting-type moves.
minds-eye.desc: The Pokémon ignores changes to opponents' evasiveness, its accuracy can't be lowered, and it can hit Ghost types with Normal- and Fighting-type moves.

minus.name: Minus
minus.effect: Ups Sp. Atk if another Pokémon has Plus or Minus.
minus.desc: Boosts the Sp. Atk stat of the Pokémon if an ally with the Plus or Minus Ability is also in battle.

mirror-armor.name: Mirror Armor
mirror-armor.desc: Bounces back only the stat-lowering effects that the Pokémon receives.

misty-surge.name: Misty Surge
misty-surge.effect: Misty Surge creates a low-lying mist, like the move Misty Terrain, when the bearer enters battle. It protects all grounded Pokémon from status conditions and halves the power of Dragon type attacks.
misty-surge.desc: Turns the ground into Misty Terrain when the Pokémon enters a battle.

mold-breaker.name: Mold Breaker
mold-breaker.effect: Mold Breaker prevents a target's ability from affecting moves that the Mold Breaker Pokémon uses. It only affects abilities that change the power, accuracy or other effects of moves.
mold-breaker.desc: The Pokémon's moves are unimpeded by the Ability of the target.

moody.name: Moody
moody.effect: Raises one stat and lowers another.
moody.desc: Every turn, one of the Pokémon's stats will be boosted sharply but another stat will be lowered.

motor-drive.name: Motor Drive
motor-drive.effect: Raises Speed if hit by an Electric-type move.
motor-drive.desc: The Pokémon takes no damage when hit by Electric-type moves. Instead, its Speed stat is boosted.

moxie.name: Moxie
moxie.effect: Moxie increases the user's Attack one stage upon fainting an opponent.
moxie.desc: When the Pokémon knocks out a target, it shows moxie, which boosts its Attack stat.

multiscale.name: Multiscale
multiscale.effect: Reduces damage when HP is full.
multiscale.desc: Reduces the amount of damage the Pokémon takes while its HP is full.

multitype.name: Multitype
multitype.effect: Multitype changes the ability-bearer's type if it is holding one of the Type Plate items. Moves of the corresponding type receive STAB.
multitype.desc: Changes the Pokémon's type to match the plate it holds.

mycelium-might.name: Mycelium Might
mycelium-might.effect: Status moves go last, but are not affected by the opponent's ability.
mycelium-might.desc: The Pokémon will always act more slowly when using status moves, but these moves will be unimpeded by the Ability of the target.

natural-cure.name: Natural Cure
natural-cure.effect: All status problems heal when it switches out.
natural-cure.desc: The Pokémon's status conditions are cured when it switches out.

neuroforce.name: Neuroforce
neuroforce.effect: Powers up moves that are super effective.
neuroforce.desc: Powers up the Pokémon's supereffective attacks even further.

neutralizing-gas.name: Neutralizing Gas
neutralizing-gas.effect: Neutralizes abilities of all Pokémon in battle.
neutralizing-gas.desc: While the Pokémon is in the battle, the effects of all other Pokémon's Abilities will be nullified or will not be triggered.

no-guard.name: No Guard
no-guard.effect: No Guard ensures that all attacks used by, and targeted at, the ability-bearer hit without fail.
no-guard.desc: The Pokémon employs no-guard tactics to ensure incoming and outgoing attacks always land.

oblivious.name: Oblivious
oblivious.effect: Oblivious makes the Pokémon immune to gender-based moves and abilities, specifically Attract, Captivate and Cute Charm.
oblivious.desc: The Pokémon is oblivious, keeping it from being infatuated, falling for taunts, or being affected by Intimidate.

opportunist.name: Opportunist
opportunist.effect: Copies stat boosts by the opponent.
opportunist.desc: If an opponent's stat is boosted, the Pokémon seizes the opportunity to boost the same stat for itself.

orichalcum-pulse.name: Orichalcum Pulse
orichalcum-pulse.effect: Turns the sunlight harsh when entering battle, and boosts Attack while active.
orichalcum-pulse.desc: Turns the sunlight harsh when the Pokémon enters a battle. The ancient pulse thrumming through the Pokémon also boosts its Attack stat in harsh sunlight.

overcoat.name: Overcoat
overcoat.effect: Overcoat makes the Pokémon immune to residual damage from weather conditions (specifically Hail and Sandstorm).
overcoat.desc: The Pokémon takes no damage from sandstorms. It is also protected from the effects of powders and spores.

overgrow.name: Overgrow
overgrow.effect: Overgrow increases the power of Grass-type moves by 50% (1.5×) when the ability-bearer's HP falls below a third of its maximum (known in-game as in a pinch).
overgrow.desc: Powers up Grass-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low.

own-tempo.name: Own Tempo
own-tempo.effect: Prevents the Pokémon from becoming confused.
own-tempo.desc: The Pokémon sticks to its own tempo, preventing it from becoming confused or being affected by Intimidate.

pickpocket.name: Pickpocket
pickpocket.effect: Steals an item when hit by another Pokémon.
pickpocket.desc: The Pokémon steals the held item from attackers that make direct contact with it.

pickup.name: Pickup
pickup.effect: When another Pokémon on the field uses a single-use held item, a Pokémon with Pickup will obtain the used item (if they are not already holding anything) and it can be used again.
pickup.desc: The Pokémon may pick up an item another Pokémon used during a battle. It may pick up items outside of battle, too.

pixilate.name: Pixilate
pixilate.effect: Pixilate causes all Normal-type attacking moves used by the Pokémon to become Fairy-type, and increase in power by 20%.
pixilate.desc: Normal-type moves become Fairy-type moves. The power of those moves is boosted a little.

plus.name: Plus
plus.effect: Ups Sp. Atk if another Pokémon has Plus or Minus.
plus.desc: Boosts the Sp. Atk stat of the Pokémon if an ally with the Plus or Minus Ability is also in battle.

poison-heal.name: Poison Heal
poison-heal.effect: Restores HP if the Pokémon is poisoned.
poison-heal.desc: If poisoned, the Pokémon has its HP restored instead of taking damage.

poison-point.name: Poison Point
poison-point.effect: Contact with the Pokémon may poison the attacker.
poison-point.desc: Contact with the Pokémon may poison the attacker.

poison-puppeteer.name: Poison Puppeteer
poison-puppeteer.effect: Pokémon poisoned by Pecharunt's moves will also become confused.
poison-puppeteer.desc: Pokémon poisoned by Pecharunt's moves will also become confused.

poison-touch.name: Poison Touch
poison-touch.effect: May poison targets when a Pokémon makes contact.
poison-touch.desc: May poison a target when the Pokémon makes contact.

power-of-alchemy.name: Power of Alchemy
power-of-alchemy.effect: The Pokémon copies the Ability of a defeated ally.
power-of-alchemy.desc: The Pokémon copies the Ability of a defeated ally.

power-spot.name: Power Spot
power-spot.effect: Just being next to the Pokémon powers up moves.
power-spot.desc: Just being next to the Pokémon powers up moves.

prankster.name: Prankster
prankster.effect: Prankster increases the priority of status moves by +1.
prankster.desc: Gives priority to the Pokémon's status moves.

pressure.name: Pressure
pressure.effect: Pressure makes any attack targeted at the ability-bearer - regardless of whether it hits - use 2 PP instead of 1.
pressure.desc: Puts other Pokémon under pressure, causing them to expend more PP to use their moves.

primordial-sea.name: Primordial Sea
primordial-sea.effect: Primordial Sea creates heavy rain when the ability is activated (by Kyogre reverting to its Primal form).
primordial-sea.desc: The Pokémon changes the weather to nullify Fire-type attacks.

prism-armor.name: Prism Armor
prism-armor.effect: Prism Armor reduces the damage taken from super-effective attacks by 25%. It is not affected by the abilities Mold Breaker, Teravolt, or Turboblaze.
prism-armor.desc: Reduces the power of supereffective attacks that hit the Pokémon.

propeller-tail.name: Propeller Tail
propeller-tail.effect: Ignores moves and abilities that draw in moves.
propeller-tail.desc: Ignores the effects of opposing Pokémon's Abilities and moves that draw in moves.

protean.name: Protean
protean.effect: Protean changes the Pokémon's type to that of its previously used attack.
protean.desc: Changes the Pokémon's type to the type of the move it's about to use. This works only once each time the Pokémon enters battle.

protosynthesis.name: Protosynthesis
protosynthesis.effect: Raises highest stat in harsh sunlight, or if holding Booster Energy.
protosynthesis.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat in harsh sunlight or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy.

psychic-surge.name: Psychic Surge
psychic-surge.effect: Psychic Surge creates a low-lying psychic field, like the move Psychic Terrain, when the Pokémon enters battle. It prevents high-priority moves being used and increases the power of Psychic type attacks.
psychic-surge.desc: Turns the ground into Psychic Terrain when the Pokémon enters a battle.

punk-rock.name: Punk Rock
punk-rock.effect: Boosts sound-based moves and halves damage from the same moves.
punk-rock.desc: Boosts the power of sound-based moves. The Pokémon also takes half the damage from these kinds of moves.

pure-power.name: Pure Power
pure-power.desc: Using its pure power, the Pokémon doubles its Attack stat.

purifying-salt.name: Purifying Salt
purifying-salt.effect: Protects from status conditions and halves damage from Ghost-type moves.
purifying-salt.desc: The Pokémon's pure salt protects it from status conditions and halves the damage taken from Ghost-type moves.

quark-drive.name: Quark Drive
quark-drive.effect: Raises highest stat on Electric Terrain, or if holding Booster Energy.
quark-drive.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's most proficient stat on Electric Terrain or if the Pokémon is holding Booster Energy.

queenly-majesty.name: Queenly Majesty
queenly-majesty.desc: The Pokémon's majesty pressures opponents and makes them unable to use priority moves against the Pokémon or its allies.

quick-draw.name: Quick Draw
quick-draw.desc: Enables the Pokémon to move first occasionally.

quick-feet.name: Quick Feet
quick-feet.effect: Quick Feet raises the ability-bearer's Speed by 50% when inflicted by a major status ailment (poison, burn, paralysis, freeze or sleep). If paralyzed, the Pokémon does not suffer the usual drop in Speed.
quick-feet.desc: Boosts the Speed stat if the Pokémon has a status condition.

rain-dish.name: Rain Dish
rain-dish.effect: A Pokémon with Rain Dish will recover 1⁄16 of its maximum HP during rain, after each turn.
rain-dish.desc: The Pokémon gradually regains HP in rain.

rattled.name: Rattled
rattled.effect: When a Pokémon with Rattled is hit by a Bug, Ghost or Dark type move, its Speed is raised one stage (up to the usual maximum of +6 stages).
rattled.desc: The Pokémon gets scared when hit by a Dark-, Ghost-, or Bug-type attack or if intimidated, which boosts its Speed stat.

receiver.name: Receiver
receiver.effect: A Pokémon with Receiver will inherit the ability of a teammate in a double/triple battle when that teammate faints.
receiver.desc: The Pokémon copies the Ability of a defeated ally.

reckless.name: Reckless
reckless.effect: Reckless increases the power of recoil moves by 20%. By extension, this means the amount of recoil damage taken will increase as more damage is dealt (except for High Jump Kick and Jump Kick which are based on the user's HP).
reckless.desc: Powers up moves that have recoil damage.

regenerator.name: Regenerator
regenerator.effect: A Pokémon with Regenerator restores 1⁄3 of its maximum HP when switching out.
regenerator.desc: The Pokémon has a little of its HP restored when withdrawn from battle.

ripen.name: Ripen
ripen.desc: Ripens Berries and doubles their effect.

rivalry.name: Rivalry
rivalry.effect: Deals more damage to a Pokémon of same gender.
rivalry.desc: The Pokémon's competitive spirit makes it deal more damage to Pokémon of the same gender, but less damage to Pokémon of the opposite gender.

rock-head.name: Rock Head
rock-head.effect: Protects the Pokémon from recoil damage.
rock-head.desc: Protects the Pokémon from recoil damage.

rocky-payload.name: Rocky Payload
rocky-payload.effect: Rocky Payload increases the power of Rock-type moves used by this Pokémon by 50%.

rough-skin.name: Rough Skin
rough-skin.effect: When a Pokémon with Rough Skin is hit by a move that makes contact, the attacker receives damage equal to 1⁄8 of their maximum HP.
rough-skin.desc: The Pokémon's rough skin damages attackers that make direct contact with it.

run-away.name: Run Away
run-away.effect: Run Away allows the bearer to flee a battle with a wild Pokémon without fail, even if the opposing Pokémon has used a move like Mean Look or Bind, or has an ability such as Arena Trap.
run-away.desc: Enables a sure getaway from wild Pokémon.

sand-force.name: Sand Force
sand-force.effect: Sand Force raises the power of Ground, Rock and Steel type moves by 30% during a sandstorm.
sand-force.desc: Boosts the power of Rock-, Ground-, and Steel-type moves in a sandstorm.

sand-rush.name: Sand Rush
sand-rush.effect: Sand Rush doubles the ability-bearer's Speed during a sandstorm.
sand-rush.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in a sandstorm.

sand-spit.name: Sand Spit
sand-spit.effect: Creates a sandstorm when hit by an attack.
sand-spit.desc: The Pokémon creates a sandstorm when it's hit by an attack.

sand-stream.name: Sand Stream
sand-stream.effect: Sand Stream creates a sandstorm when the ability-bearer enters battle. The effect lasts 5 turns, unless it is cleared via Air Lock or Cloud Nine or replaced by another weather condition.
sand-stream.desc: The Pokémon summons a sandstorm when it enters a battle.

sand-veil.name: Sand Veil
sand-veil.effect: Sand Veil raises the ability-bearer's evasion by 20% in a sandstorm. It also gives immunity to sandstorm damage (if they are not already protected by being Ground/Rock/Steel type).
sand-veil.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness in a sandstorm.

sap-sipper.name: Sap Sipper
sap-sipper.effect: Boosts Attack when hit by a Grass-type move.
sap-sipper.desc: The Pokémon takes no damage when hit by Grass-type moves. Instead, its Attack stat is boosted.

scrappy.name: Scrappy
scrappy.effect: Enables moves to hit Ghost-type Pokémon.
scrappy.desc: The Pokémon can hit Ghost-type Pokémon with Normal- and Fighting-type moves. It is also unaffected by Intimidate.

seed-sower.name: Seed Sower
seed-sower.effect: Turns the ground into Grassy Terrain when the Pokémon is hit by an attack.
seed-sower.desc: Turns the ground into Grassy Terrain when the Pokémon is hit by an attack.

serene-grace.name: Serene Grace
serene-grace.effect: Serene Grace doubles the chance of moves' secondary effects occurring - specifically stat changes, status ailments, or flinching. It also increases the chance of flinching due to the held items King's Rock and Razor Fang from 10% to 20% (however, note that those items do not affect moves that already have a flinch chance).
serene-grace.desc: Raises the likelihood of additional effects occurring when the Pokémon uses its moves.

shadow-shield.name: Shadow Shield
shadow-shield.effect: Reduces damage when HP is full.
shadow-shield.desc: Reduces the amount of damage the Pokémon takes while its HP is full.

shadow-tag.name: Shadow Tag
shadow-tag.desc: The Pokémon steps on the opposing Pokémon's shadows to prevent them from fleeing or switching out.

sharpness.name: Sharpness
sharpness.effect: Sharpness increases the power of all slicing moves by 50%.

shed-skin.name: Shed Skin
shed-skin.effect: The Pokémon may heal its own status problems.
shed-skin.desc: The Pokémon may cure its own status conditions by shedding its skin.

sheer-force.name: Sheer Force
sheer-force.effect: Sheer Force increases the power of moves that have beneficial secondary effects by 30%, but removes those additional effects.
sheer-force.desc: Removes any additional effects from the Pokémon's moves, but increases the moves' power.

shell-armor.name: Shell Armor
shell-armor.effect: Shell Armor prevents the Pokémon from receiving a critical hit.
shell-armor.desc: A hard shell protects the Pokémon from critical hits.

shield-dust.name: Shield Dust
shield-dust.effect: Blocks the added effects of attacks taken.
shield-dust.desc: Protective dust shields the Pokémon from the additional effects of moves.

shields-down.name: Shields Down
shields-down.effect: Shields Down causes the Pokémon to changes its appearance and stats depending on its remaining HP.
shields-down.desc: When its HP drops to half or less, the Pokémon's shell breaks and it becomes aggressive.

simple.name: Simple
simple.effect: The Simple ability doubles the number of stages of all stat changes. Stats can be raised to a maximum of +6 stages each, or lowered to a minimum of -6 stages each.For example, using Swords Dance would increase the Pokémon's attack by 4 stages instead of the usual 2. If Tail Whip was targeted at a Pokémon with Simple, its Defense would drop 2 stages instead of 1.The move Simple Beam can change a Pokémon's ability to Simple.
simple.desc: Doubles the effects of the Pokémon's stat changes.

skill-link.name: Skill Link
skill-link.effect: Skill Link causes multi-strike moves to always hit their maximum number of times. The moves affected are listed below; note that moves such as Double Kick that always strike the same number of times are not affected.
skill-link.desc: Maximizes the number of times multistrike moves hit.

slow-start.name: Slow Start
slow-start.desc: For five turns, the Pokémon's Attack and Speed stats are halved.

slush-rush.name: Slush Rush
slush-rush.effect: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in a hailstorm.
slush-rush.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in snow.

sniper.name: Sniper
sniper.effect: Sniper increases the power of critical hits by 1.5×. This means a critical hit will deal 2.25× normal damage instead of 1.5×.
sniper.desc: If the Pokémon's attack lands a critical hit, the attack is powered up even further.

snow-cloak.name: Snow Cloak
snow-cloak.effect: Snow Cloak raises ability-bearer's evasion by 20% in a hail storm. It also gives immunity to damage by hail (if they are not already protected by being Ice type).
snow-cloak.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness in snow.

snow-warning.name: Snow Warning
snow-warning.effect: Snow Warning creates a hailstorm when the ability-bearer enters battle. The effect lasts 5 turns, unless it is cleared via Air Lock or Cloud Nine or replaced by another weather condition.
snow-warning.desc: The Pokémon makes it snow when it enters a battle.

solar-power.name: Solar Power
solar-power.effect: During harsh sunlight, Solar Power raises the ability-bearer's Special Attack by 50%, but it also loses 1⁄8 of its maximum HP after each turn.
solar-power.desc: In harsh sunlight, the Pokémon's Sp. Atk stat is boosted, but its HP decreases every turn.

solid-rock.name: Solid Rock
solid-rock.effect: Solid Rock reduces the damage taken from super-effective attacks by 25%.For example, a Water-type move used against a Rock-type Pokémon with Solid Rock would deal 1.5× the usual damage instead of 2×. A double weakness would be reduced from 4× to 3×.
solid-rock.desc: Reduces the power of supereffective attacks that hit the Pokémon.

soul-heart.name: Soul-Heart
soul-heart.effect: Soul-Heart raises the bearer's Special Attack one stage when any Pokémon on the field faints.
soul-heart.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's Sp. Atk stat every time another Pokémon faints.

soundproof.name: Soundproof
soundproof.effect: Soundproof grants the Pokémon immunity to all sound-based moves, preventing all damage and effects.
soundproof.desc: Soundproofing gives the Pokémon full immunity to all sound-based moves.

speed-boost.name: Speed Boost
speed-boost.effect: Its Speed stat is gradually boosted.
speed-boost.desc: The Pokémon's Speed stat is boosted every turn.

stakeout.name: Stakeout
stakeout.effect: Stakeout enables the Pokémon to deal twice the normal damage to any Pokémon that switches in or enters the field mid-battle.
stakeout.desc: Doubles the damage dealt to a target that has just switched into battle.

stall.name: Stall
stall.effect: The Pokémon moves after all other Pokémon do.
stall.desc: The Pokémon is always the last to use its moves.

stalwart.name: Stalwart
stalwart.effect: Ignores moves and abilities that draw in moves.
stalwart.desc: Ignores the effects of opposing Pokémon's Abilities and moves that draw in moves.

stamina.name: Stamina
stamina.effect: Stamina raises the bearer's Defense by one stage when it is attacked by any move.
stamina.desc: Boosts the Defense stat when the Pokémon is hit by an attack.

static.name: Static
static.effect: If a Pokémon with Static is hit by a move making contact, there is a 30% chance the foe will become paralyzed.
static.desc: The Pokémon is charged with static electricity and may paralyze attackers that make direct contact with it.

steadfast.name: Steadfast
steadfast.effect: Raises Speed each time the Pokémon flinches.
steadfast.desc: The Pokémon's determination boosts its Speed stat every time it flinches.

steam-engine.name: Steam Engine
steam-engine.effect: Steam Engine raises the user's Speed by three stages when it is hit by a Fire- or Water-type attack. The attack still deals damage.
steam-engine.desc: Boosts the Speed stat drastically when the Pokémon is hit by a Fire- or Water-type move.

steely-spirit.name: Steely Spirit
steely-spirit.effect: Powers up ally Pokémon's Steel-type moves.
steely-spirit.desc: Powers up the Steel-type moves of the Pokémon and its allies.

stench.name: Stench
stench.effect: A Pokémon with Stench has a 10% chance of causing the opponent to flinch when hit by a damaging move (provided the ability-bearer strikes first as usual).
stench.desc: By releasing a stench when attacking, the Pokémon may cause the target to flinch.

sticky-hold.name: Sticky Hold
sticky-hold.effect: Sticky Hold prevents held items from being taken or switched.
sticky-hold.desc: The Pokémon's held items cling to its sticky body and cannot be removed by other Pokémon.

storm-drain.name: Storm Drain
storm-drain.effect: Storm Drain forces all single-target Water-type moves - used by any other Pokémon on the field - to target this Pokémon, and with 100% accuracy. The ability is most useful in double/triple battles.
storm-drain.desc: The Pokémon draws in all Water-type moves. Instead of taking damage from them, its Sp. Atk stat is boosted.

strong-jaw.name: Strong Jaw
strong-jaw.effect: Strong Jaw increases the power of all biting moves by 50%.
strong-jaw.desc: The Pokémon's strong jaw boosts the power of its biting moves.

sturdy.name: Sturdy
sturdy.effect: Sturdy allows the Pokémon to survive with 1 HP if attacked at full HP with an attack that would otherwise knock it out. It also prevents One-Hit-KO moves (Fissure, Horn Drill, Guillotine or Sheer Cold).
sturdy.desc: The Pokémon cannot be knocked out by a single hit as long as its HP is full. One-hit KO moves will also fail to knock it out.

suction-cups.name: Suction Cups
suction-cups.effect: Suction Cups prevents opponents forcing the ability-bearer to switch out or flee via the moves Roar, Whirlwind, Circle Throw, or Dragon Tail, or the item Red Card.
suction-cups.desc: The Pokémon uses suction cups to stay in one spot. This protects it from moves and items that would force it to switch out.

super-luck.name: Super Luck
super-luck.effect: Super Luck raises the ability-bearer's critical-hit ratio by one stage (for most moves this increases from a 1⁄16 chance to 1⁄8).
super-luck.desc: The Pokémon is so lucky that the critical-hit ratios of its moves are boosted.

supersweet-syrup.name: Supersweet Syrup
supersweet-syrup.effect: A sickly sweet scent spreads across the field the first time the Pokémon enters a battle, lowering the evasiveness of opposing Pokémon.
supersweet-syrup.desc: A sickly sweet scent spreads across the field the first time the Pokémon enters a battle, lowering the evasiveness of opposing Pokémon.

supreme-overlord.name: Supreme Overlord
supreme-overlord.effect: Attack and Special Attack are boosted for each party Pokémon that has been defeated.
supreme-overlord.desc: When the Pokémon enters a battle, its Attack and Sp. Atk stats are slightly boosted for each of the allies in its party that have already been defeated.

surge-surfer.name: Surge Surfer
surge-surfer.effect: Surge Surfer doubles the bearer's Speed when Electric Terrain is active.
surge-surfer.desc: Doubles the Pokémon's Speed stat on Electric Terrain.

swarm.name: Swarm
swarm.effect: Swarm increases the power of Bug-type moves by 50% (1.5×) when the ability-bearer's HP falls below a third of its maximum (known in-game as in a pinch).
swarm.desc: Powers up Bug-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low.

sweet-veil.name: Sweet Veil
sweet-veil.effect: Sweet Veil prevents this Pokémon and its allies from falling asleep, for example from moves like Hypnosis.
sweet-veil.desc: Prevents the Pokémon and its allies from falling asleep.

swift-swim.name: Swift Swim
swift-swim.effect: Swift Swim doubles the ability-bearer's Speed during rain.
swift-swim.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's Speed stat in rain.

sword-of-ruin.name: Sword of Ruin
sword-of-ruin.effect: Lowers Defense of all Pokémon except itself.
sword-of-ruin.desc: The power of the Pokémon's ruinous sword lowers the Defense stats of all Pokémon except itself.

symbiosis.name: Symbiosis
symbiosis.effect: The Pokémon can pass an item to an ally.
symbiosis.desc: The Pokémon passes its held item to an ally that has used up an item.

synchronize.name: Synchronize
synchronize.effect: If the opponent causes a burn, paralysis, or poisoning of a Pokémon with Synchronize, the opponent receives the status condition too. Self-inflicted status conditions (for example through the use of an item) are not passed on.
synchronize.desc: If the Pokémon is burned, paralyzed, or poisoned by another Pokémon, that Pokémon will be inflicted with the same status condition.

tablets-of-ruin.name: Tablets of Ruin
tablets-of-ruin.effect: Lowers Attack of all Pokémon except itself.
tablets-of-ruin.desc: The power of the Pokémon's ruinous wooden tablets lowers the Attack stats of all Pokémon except itself.

tangled-feet.name: Tangled Feet
tangled-feet.effect: Raises evasion if the Pokémon is confused.
tangled-feet.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's evasiveness if it is confused.

tangling-hair.name: Tangling Hair
tangling-hair.effect: Contact with the Pokémon lowers the attacker's Speed stat.
tangling-hair.desc: Contact with the Pokémon lowers the attacker's Speed stat.

technician.name: Technician
technician.effect: Technician increases the power of moves - that are usually base power 60 or below - by 50%.
technician.desc: Powers up weak moves so the Pokémon can deal more damage with them.

telepathy.name: Telepathy
telepathy.effect: Pokémon with the Telepathy ability will not take damage from teammates in double and triple battles.
telepathy.desc: The Pokémon anticipates and dodges the attacks of its allies.

tera-shell.name: Tera Shell
tera-shell.effect: The Pokémon's shell contains the powers of each type. All damage-dealing moves that hit the Pokémon when its HP is full will not be very effective.
tera-shell.desc: The Pokémon's shell contains the powers of each type. All damage-dealing moves that hit the Pokémon when its HP is full will not be very effective.

tera-shift.name: Tera Shift
tera-shift.effect: When the Pokémon enters a battle, it absorbs the energy around itself and transforms into its Terastal Form.
tera-shift.desc: When the Pokémon enters a battle, it absorbs the energy around itself and transforms into its Terastal Form.

teraform-zero.name: Teraform Zero
teraform-zero.effect: When Terapagos changes into its Stellar Form, it uses its hidden powers to eliminate all effects of weather and terrain, reducing them to zero.
teraform-zero.desc: When Terapagos changes into its Stellar Form, it uses its hidden powers to eliminate all effects of weather and terrain, reducing them to zero.

teravolt.name: Teravolt
teravolt.effect: Teravolt prevents a target's ability from affecting moves that the Teravolt Pokémon uses. It only affects abilities that change the power, accuracy or other effects of moves.
teravolt.desc: The Pokémon's moves are unimpeded by the Ability of the target.

thermal-exchange.name: Thermal Exchange
thermal-exchange.effect: Raises Attack when hit by a Fire-type move. Cannot be burned.
thermal-exchange.desc: Boosts the Attack stat when the Pokémon is hit by a Fire-type move. The Pokémon also cannot be burned.

thick-fat.name: Thick Fat
thick-fat.effect: Thick Fat reduces the damage taken from Fire-type and Ice-type moves by 50%.
thick-fat.desc: The Pokémon is protected by a layer of thick fat, which halves the damage taken from Fire- and Ice-type moves.

tinted-lens.name: Tinted Lens
tinted-lens.desc: The Pokémon can use “not very effective” moves to deal regular damage.

torrent.name: Torrent
torrent.effect: Torrent increases the power of Water-type moves by 50% (1.5×) when the ability-bearer's HP falls below a third of its maximum (known in-game as in a pinch).
torrent.desc: Powers up Water-type moves when the Pokémon's HP is low.

tough-claws.name: Tough Claws
tough-claws.effect: Tough Claws increases the power of moves that make contact.
tough-claws.desc: Powers up moves that make direct contact.

toxic-boost.name: Toxic Boost
toxic-boost.effect: Powers up physical attacks when poisoned.
toxic-boost.desc: Powers up physical moves when the Pokémon is poisoned.

toxic-chain.name: Toxic Chain
toxic-chain.effect: Toxic Chain may cause bad poisoning when the Pokémon hits an opponent with a move.
toxic-chain.desc: Toxic Chain may cause bad poisoning when the Pokémon hits an opponent with a move.

toxic-debris.name: Toxic Debris
toxic-debris.effect: Scatters poison spikes at the feet of the opposing team when the Pokémon takes damage from physical moves.
toxic-debris.desc: Scatters poison spikes at the feet of the opposing team when the Pokémon takes damage from physical moves.

trace.name: Trace
trace.effect: The Pokémon copies a foe's Ability.
trace.desc: When it enters a battle, the Pokémon copies an opposing Pokémon's Ability.

transistor.name: Transistor
transistor.effect: Transistor increases the power of Electric-type moves used by this Pokémon by 50%.

triage.name: Triage
triage.effect: Triage increases the priority of HP-restoring moves to +3, when used by the ability-bearer.
triage.desc: Gives priority to the Pokémon's healing moves.

truant.name: Truant
truant.effect: Truant causes the ability-bearer to only attack every alternate turn. On the even turns, it will say the Pokémon is loafing around.
truant.desc: Each time the Pokémon uses a move, it spends the next turn loafing around.

turboblaze.name: Turboblaze
turboblaze.effect: Turboblaze prevents a target's ability from affecting moves that the Turboblaze Pokémon uses. It only affects abilities that change the power, accuracy or other effects of moves.
turboblaze.desc: The Pokémon's moves are unimpeded by the Ability of the target.

unaware.name: Unaware
unaware.effect: Ignores any stat changes in the Pokémon.
unaware.desc: When attacking, the Pokémon ignores the target's stat changes.

unburden.name: Unburden
unburden.effect: Raises Speed if a held item is used.
unburden.desc: Boosts the Speed stat if the Pokémon's held item is used or lost.

unnerve.name: Unnerve
unnerve.effect: Makes the foe nervous and unable to eat Berries.
unnerve.desc: Unnerves opposing Pokémon and makes them unable to eat Berries.

unseen-fist.name: Unseen Fist
unseen-fist.effect: Contact moves can strike through Protect/Detect.
unseen-fist.desc: If the Pokémon uses moves that make direct contact, it can attack the target even if the target protects itself.

vessel-of-ruin.name: Vessel of Ruin
vessel-of-ruin.effect: Lowers Special Attack of all Pokémon except itself.
vessel-of-ruin.desc: The power of the Pokémon's ruinous vessel lowers the Sp. Atk stats of all Pokémon except itself.

vital-spirit.name: Vital Spirit
vital-spirit.effect: Vital Spirit prevents the ability-bearer from falling asleep. This means that it also prevents the use of the move Rest.
vital-spirit.desc: The Pokémon is full of vitality, and that prevents it from falling asleep.

volt-absorb.name: Volt Absorb
volt-absorb.effect: A Pokémon with Volt Absorb heals 1⁄4 of its maximum HP when hit by an Electric-type attack, including Thunder Wave.
volt-absorb.desc: If hit by an Electric-type move, the Pokémon has its HP restored instead of taking damage.

water-absorb.name: Water Absorb
water-absorb.effect: A Pokémon with Water Absorb heals 1⁄4 of its maximum HP when hit by a Water-type attack.
water-absorb.desc: If hit by a Water-type move, the Pokémon has its HP restored instead of taking damage.

water-bubble.name: Water Bubble
water-bubble.effect: Water Bubble reduces damage taken from Fire-type moves by 50%, and doubles the power of Water-type moves used by the ability-bearer. It also prevents the Pokémon from being burned.
water-bubble.desc: Lowers the power of Fire-type moves that hit the Pokémon and prevents it from being burned.

water-compaction.name: Water Compaction
water-compaction.effect: Water Compaction raises the bearer's Defense by 2 stages when it is hit by a Water-type move.
water-compaction.desc: Boosts the Defense stat sharply when the Pokémon is hit by a Water-type move.

water-veil.name: Water Veil
water-veil.effect: Prevents the Pokémon from getting a burn.
water-veil.desc: The Pokémon's water veil prevents it from being burned.

weak-armor.name: Weak Armor
weak-armor.effect: When a Pokémon with Weak Armor is hit by a physical move, its Defense drops one stage, but its Speed increases by one stage.
weak-armor.desc: The Pokémon's Defense stat is lowered when it takes damage from physical moves, but its Speed stat is sharply boosted.

well-baked-body.name: Well-Baked Body
well-baked-body.effect: Immune to Fire-type moves, and Defense is sharply boosted.
well-baked-body.desc: The Pokémon takes no damage when hit by Fire-type moves. Instead, its Defense stat is sharply boosted.

white-smoke.name: White Smoke
white-smoke.effect: Prevents other Pokémon from lowering its stats.
white-smoke.desc: The Pokémon is protected by its white smoke, which prevents other Pokémon from lowering its stats.

wind-power.name: Wind Power
wind-power.effect: If a Pokémon with Wind Power is hit by a wind move, the power of the next Electric-type move it uses is doubled.
wind-power.desc: The Pokémon becomes charged when it is hit by a wind move, boosting the power of the next Electric-type move the Pokémon uses.

wind-rider.name: Wind Rider
wind-rider.effect: Wind Rider gives immunity to wind moves, and causes the Pokémon's Attack to increase by one stage when hit by one.
wind-rider.desc: Boosts the Pokémon's Attack stat if Tailwind takes effect or if the Pokémon is hit by a wind move. The Pokémon also takes no damage from wind moves.

wonder-skin.name: Wonder Skin
wonder-skin.effect: Wonder Skin halves the accuracy of all status moves targeted at the ability-bearer.
wonder-skin.desc: Makes status moves more likely to miss the Pokémon.

zero-to-hero.name: Zero to Hero
zero-to-hero.effect: Transforms into its Hero Form when switching out.
zero-to-hero.desc: The Pokémon transforms into its Hero Form when it switches out.

cond.use: Psyshield Bash 20 times in Agile Style

absorb.name: Absorb
absorb.desc: A nutrient-draining attack. The user's HP is restored by up to half the damage taken by the target.

accelerock.name: Accelerock
accelerock.desc: The user smashes into the target at high speed. This move always goes first.

acid-armor.name: Acid Armor
acid-armor.desc: The user alters its cellular structure to liquefy itself, sharply boosting its Defense stat.

acid-spray.name: Acid Spray
acid-spray.desc: The user attacks by spitting fluid that works to melt the target. This also harshly lowers the target's Sp. Def stat.

acid.name: Acid
acid.desc: Opposing Pokémon are attacked with a spray of harsh acid. This may also lower their Sp. Def stats.

acrobatics.name: Acrobatics
acrobatics.desc: The user nimbly strikes the target. This attack does massive damage if the user isn't holding an item.

acupressure.name: Acupressure
acupressure.desc: The user applies pressure to stress points, sharply boosting one of its or its allies' stats.

aerial-ace.name: Aerial Ace
aerial-ace.desc: The user confounds the target with speed, then slashes. This attack never misses.

aeroblast.name: Aeroblast
aeroblast.desc: A vortex of air is shot at the target to inflict damage. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

after-you.name: After You
after-you.desc: The user helps the target and makes it use its move right after the user.

agility.name: Agility
agility.desc: The user relaxes and lightens its body to move faster. This sharply boosts its Speed stat.

air-cutter.name: Air Cutter
air-cutter.desc: The user launches razor-like wind to slash opposing Pokémon. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

air-slash.name: Air Slash
air-slash.desc: The user attacks with a blade of air that slices even the sky. This may also make the target flinch.

alluring-voice.name: Alluring Voice
alluring-voice.desc: The user attacks the target using its angelic voice. This also confuses the target if its stats have been boosted during the turn.

ally-switch.name: Ally Switch
ally-switch.desc: The user teleports using a strange power and switches places with one of its allies. This move's chance of failing rises if it is used in succession.

amnesia.name: Amnesia
amnesia.desc: The user temporarily empties its mind to forget its concerns. This sharply boosts the user's Sp. Def stat.

ancient-power.name: Ancient Power
ancient-power.desc: The user attacks with a prehistoric power. This may also boost all the user's stats at once.

apple-acid.name: Apple Acid
apple-acid.desc: The user attacks the target with an acidic liquid created from tart apples. This also lowers the target's Sp. Def stat.

aqua-cutter.name: Aqua Cutter
aqua-cutter.desc: The user expels pressurized water to cut at the target like a blade. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

aqua-jet.name: Aqua Jet
aqua-jet.desc: The user lunges at the target to inflict damage, moving at blinding speed. This move always goes first.

aqua-ring.name: Aqua Ring
aqua-ring.desc: The user envelops itself in a veil made of water. It regains some HP every turn.

aqua-step.name: Aqua Step
aqua-step.desc: The user toys with the target and attacks it using light and fluid dance steps. This also boosts the user's Speed stat.

aqua-tail.name: Aqua Tail
aqua-tail.desc: The user attacks by swinging its tail as if it were a vicious wave in a raging storm.

arm-thrust.name: Arm Thrust
arm-thrust.desc: The user attacks the target with open-palmed arm thrusts. This move hits two to five times in a row.

armor-cannon.name: Armor Cannon
armor-cannon.desc: The user shoots its own armor out as blazing projectiles. This also lowers the user's Defense and Sp. Def stats.

aromatic-mist.name: Aromatic Mist
aromatic-mist.desc: The user boosts the Sp. Def stat of an ally Pokémon by using a mysterious aroma.

assurance.name: Assurance
assurance.desc: This move's power is doubled if the target has already taken some damage in the same turn.

astonish.name: Astonish
astonish.desc: The user attacks the target by crying out in a startling fashion. This may also make the target flinch.

astral-barrage.name: Astral Barrage
astral-barrage.desc: The user attacks by sending a frightful amount of small ghosts at opposing Pokémon.

attack-order.name: Attack Order
attack-order.desc: The user calls out its underlings to pummel the target. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

attract.name: Attract
attract.desc: If the target is of the opposite gender to the user, it becomes infatuated with the user and will sometimes be unable to use its moves.

aura-sphere.name: Aura Sphere
aura-sphere.desc: The user lets loose a pulse of aura power from deep within its body at the target. This attack never misses.

aura-wheel.name: Aura Wheel
aura-wheel.desc: Morpeko attacks and boosts its Speed stat with the energy stored in its cheeks. This move's type changes depending on the user's form.

aurora-beam.name: Aurora Beam
aurora-beam.desc: The target is hit with a rainbow-colored beam. This may also lower the target's Attack stat.

aurora-veil.name: Aurora Veil
aurora-veil.desc: This move reduces damage from physical and special moves for five turns. This can be used only when it is snowing.

avalanche.name: Avalanche
avalanche.desc: This move's power is doubled if the target has inflicted damage on the user in the same turn.

axe-kick.name: Axe Kick
axe-kick.desc: The user attacks by kicking up into the air and slamming its heel down upon the target. This may also confuse the target. If it misses, the user takes damage instead.

baby-doll-eyes.name: Baby-doll Eyes
baby-doll-eyes.desc: The user stares at the target with its baby-doll eyes, which lowers the target's Attack stat. This move always goes first.

baneful-bunker.name: Baneful Bunker
baneful-bunker.desc: In addition to protecting the user from attacks, this move also poisons any attacker that makes direct contact.

barb-barrage.name: Barb Barrage
barb-barrage.desc: The user launches countless toxic barbs to inflict damage. This may also poison the target. This move's power is doubled if the target is already poisoned.

baton-pass.name: Baton Pass
baton-pass.desc: The user switches places with a party Pokémon in waiting and passes along any stat changes.

beak-blast.name: Beak Blast
beak-blast.desc: The user first heats up its beak, and then it attacks the target. Making direct contact with the user while it's heating up its beak results in a burn.

beat-up.name: Beat Up
beat-up.desc: The user gets all party Pokémon to attack the target. The more party Pokémon, the greater the number of attacks.

belch.name: Belch
belch.desc: The user lets out a damaging belch at the target. The user must eat a held Berry to use this move.

belly-drum.name: Belly Drum
belly-drum.desc: The user maximizes its Attack stat but loses HP equal to half its max HP.

bind.name: Bind
bind.desc: A long body, tentacles, or the like are used to bind and squeeze the target for four to five turns.

bite.name: Bite
bite.desc: The target is bitten with viciously sharp fangs. This may also make the target flinch.

bitter-blade.name: Bitter Blade
bitter-blade.desc: The user focuses its bitter feelings toward the world of the living into a slashing attack. The user's HP is restored by up to half the damage taken by the target.

bitter-malice.name: Bitter Malice
bitter-malice.desc: The user attacks the target with spine-chilling resentment. This also lowers the target's Attack stat.

blast-burn.name: Blast Burn
blast-burn.desc: The target is razed by a fiery explosion. The user can't move on the next turn.

blaze-kick.name: Blaze Kick
blaze-kick.desc: The user launches a kick that has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit. This may also leave the target with a burn.

bleakwind-storm.name: Bleakwind Storm
bleakwind-storm.desc: The user attacks with savagely cold winds that cause both body and spirit to tremble. This may also lower the Speed stats of opposing Pokémon.

blizzard.name: Blizzard
blizzard.desc: A howling blizzard is summoned to strike opposing Pokémon. This may also leave the opposing Pokémon frozen.

block.name: Block
block.desc: The user blocks the target's way with arms spread wide to prevent the target from fleeing.

blood-moon.name: Blood Moon
blood-moon.desc: The user unleashes the full brunt of its spirit from a full moon that shines as red as blood. This move can't be used twice in a row.

blue-flare.name: Blue Flare
blue-flare.desc: The user attacks by engulfing the target in an intense, yet beautiful, blue flame. This may also leave the target with a burn.

body-press.name: Body Press
body-press.desc: The user attacks by slamming its body into the target. The higher the user's Defense stat, the greater the damage this move deals.

body-slam.name: Body Slam
body-slam.desc: The user attacks by dropping onto the target with its full body weight. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

bolt-strike.name: Bolt Strike
bolt-strike.desc: The user surrounds itself with a great amount of electricity and charges the target. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

bone-rush.name: Bone Rush
bone-rush.desc: The user attacks by striking the target with a hard bone. This move hits two to five times in a row.

boomburst.name: Boomburst
boomburst.desc: The user attacks everything around it with the destructive power of a terrible explosive sound.

bounce.name: Bounce
bounce.desc: The user bounces up high on the first turn, then drops onto the target on the next turn. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

branch-poke.name: Branch Poke
branch-poke.desc: The user attacks the target by poking it with a sharply pointed branch.

brave-bird.name: Brave Bird
brave-bird.desc: The user tucks in its wings and charges at a low altitude. This also damages the user quite a lot.

breaking-swipe.name: Breaking Swipe
breaking-swipe.desc: The user swings its tough tail wildly and attacks opposing Pokémon. This also lowers their Attack stats.

brick-break.name: Brick Break
brick-break.desc: The user attacks with a swift chop. This move can also break barriers, such as Light Screen and Reflect.

brine.name: Brine
brine.desc: This move's power is doubled if the target's HP is at half or less.

brutal-swing.name: Brutal Swing
brutal-swing.desc: The user swings its body around violently to inflict damage on everything in its vicinity.

bubble-beam.name: Bubble Beam
bubble-beam.desc: A spray of bubbles is forcefully ejected at the target. This may also lower the target's Speed stat.

bug-bite.name: Bug Bite
bug-bite.desc: The user attacks by biting the target. If the target is holding a Berry, the user eats it and gains its effect.

bug-buzz.name: Bug Buzz
bug-buzz.desc: The user vibrates to generate a damaging sound wave. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

bulk-up.name: Bulk Up
bulk-up.desc: The user tenses its muscles to bulk up its body, boosting its Attack and Defense stats.

bulldoze.name: Bulldoze
bulldoze.desc: The user strikes everything around it by stomping down on the ground. This lowers the Speed stats of those hit.

bullet-punch.name: Bullet Punch
bullet-punch.desc: The user strikes the target with tough punches as fast as bullets. This move always goes first.

bullet-seed.name: Bullet Seed
bullet-seed.desc: The user attacks by forcefully shooting seeds at the target. This move hits two to five times in a row.

burning-bulwark.name: Burning Bulwark
burning-bulwark.desc: The user's intensely hot fur protects it from attacks and also burns any attacker that makes direct contact with it.

burning-jealousy.name: Burning Jealousy
burning-jealousy.desc: The user attacks with energy from jealousy. This leaves all opposing Pokémon that have had their stats boosted during the turn with a burn.

calm-mind.name: Calm Mind
calm-mind.desc: The user quietly focuses its mind and calms its spirit to boost its Sp. Atk and Sp. Def stats.

ceaseless-edge.name: Ceaseless Edge
ceaseless-edge.desc: The user slashes its shell blade at the target. Shell splinters left behind by this attack remain scattered under the target as spikes.

celebrate.name: Celebrate
celebrate.desc: The Pokémon congratulates you on your special day!

charge-beam.name: Charge Beam
charge-beam.desc: The user attacks the target with an electric charge. The residual electricity may also boost the user's Sp. Atk stat.

charge.name: Charge
charge.desc: The user becomes charged, boosting the power of the next Electric-type move it uses. This also boosts the user's Sp. Def stat.

charm.name: Charm
charm.desc: The user gazes at the target rather charmingly, making it less wary. This harshly lowers the target's Attack stat.

chilling-water.name: Chilling Water
chilling-water.desc: The user attacks the target by showering it with water that's so cold it saps the target's power. This also lowers the target's Attack stat.

chilly-reception.name: Chilly Reception
chilly-reception.desc: The user tells a chillingly bad joke before switching places with a party Pokémon in waiting. This summons a snowstorm lasting five turns.

chloroblast.name: Chloroblast
chloroblast.desc: The user launches its amassed chlorophyll to inflict damage on the target. This also damages the user.

circle-throw.name: Circle Throw
circle-throw.desc: The target is thrown, and a different Pokémon is dragged out. In the wild, this ends a battle against a single Pokémon.

clanging-scales.name: Clanging Scales
clanging-scales.desc: The user rubs the scales on its entire body and makes a huge noise to attack opposing Pokémon. The user's Defense stat is lowered after the attack.

clangorous-soul.name: Clangorous Soul
clangorous-soul.desc: The user boosts all its stats by using some of its own HP.

clear-smog.name: Clear Smog
clear-smog.desc: The user attacks the target by throwing a clump of special mud. All stat changes are eliminated.

close-combat.name: Close Combat
close-combat.desc: The user fights the target up close, inflicting damage without guarding itself. This also lowers the user's Defense and Sp. Def stats.

coaching.name: Coaching
coaching.desc: The user properly coaches its ally Pokémon, boosting their Attack and Defense stats.

coil.name: Coil
coil.desc: The user coils up and concentrates. This boosts its Attack and Defense stats as well as its accuracy.

collision-course.name: Collision Course
collision-course.desc: The user transforms and crashes to the ground, causing a massive prehistoric explosion. This move's power is boosted more than usual if it's a supereffective hit.

comeuppance.name: Comeuppance
comeuppance.desc: The user retaliates with much greater force against the opponent that last inflicted damage on it.

confide.name: Confide
confide.desc: The user tells the target a secret, and the target loses its ability to concentrate. This lowers the target's Sp. Atk stat.

confuse-ray.name: Confuse Ray
